newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: European feeds remain calm despite weaker dollar.
newsitem.headline: European feeds remain calm despite weaker dollar.

text.p: A weaker dollar failed to spark much activity on the European meals and feeds market due to a lower Chicago soymeal futures opening this afternoon, market sources said.
"We saw some prodaric trades in most products, while some more activity was seen in EU rapemeal on technical covering," one broker said.
Nov EU rapemeal traded at 0.25 marks up at 29.25 marks per 100 kg fob lower Rhine, Dec at 29 and Feb/April at 28.90 marks.
A small lot afloat Argentine soymeal pellets traded at $265 a tonne cif Rotterdam.
Afloat citruspulp pellets changed hands at $114 a tonne fob Rotterdam and Nov at $109.50 cif.
Afloat Thai tapioca pellets traded at 20.25 marks per 100 kg fob lower Rhine.--KAREL LUIMES +31 20 504 5832
